1 pound Broccoli Crowns
8 ounce Sargento® 4 Cheese Mexican Shredded
1 teaspoon Cooking Oil
Salt
Pepper

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

Wash and dry produce. Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.

Toss on a baking sheet with a drizzle of cooking oil, salt, and pepper.

Roast on middle rack until lightly browned and crisp, 15-20 minutes, tossing halfway through.

In the last 1-2 minutes of cooking, sprinkle broccoli with Mexican cheese blend and continue roasting until cheese has melted.

**Recipe Suggestion:** In step 3, toss broccoli with oil, salt, pepper, and Southwest Spice.